# Lab Values educational depth

The Labs ecosystem (`/app/labs`, `labs-engine`) must deliver **adaptive clinical interpretation training**, not isolated normal ranges or static tables.

## Must teach

- Interpretation, pattern recognition, clinical reasoning  
- Relationships **between** labs and combined abnormality patterns  
- Pathophysiology correlations, prioritization, trend analysis, bedside significance  
- Nursing implications, medication implications, deterioration indicators  
- **NGN-style** judgment where lesson format supports it  
- **ECG / telemetry correlations** where clinically appropriate (e.g. electrolytes, cardiac markers)

## Must avoid as primary experience

- Range-only memorization, superficial flashcards, spreadsheet-first layouts  
- Teaching norms without **context, escalation, and trend meaning**

## Tier scaling (use existing `tierFocus` / track fields)

| Track | Emphasis |
|-------|----------|
| **RN** | Broad interpretation, prioritization, NCLEX/clinical readiness |
| **PN/RPN** | Bedside recognition, practical escalation, stable vs unpredictable client |
| **NP** | Deeper diagnostic reasoning, pathophysiology, advanced trends |
| **Allied** | Profession-aware depth |
| **New Grad** | Unit/specialty framing, ICU/ER/telemetry integration, deterioration cues |

*(New Grad may map to pathway metadata + RN depth — do not fork routes.)*

## Integrated reasoning examples (content targets)

Hgb+Hct coherence; viral vs bacterial patterns; neutrophilia; bandemia; left vs right shift; sepsis indicators; dilutional states; renal injury progression; electrolyte + ECG; ABG; inflammatory markers; liver patterns; coagulation; cardiac marker progression.

## Ecosystem integration

Labs content and CTAs should link naturally into ECG, telemetry, med safety, NGN, simulations, OSCE, adaptive remediation, and future report-card mastery — **reuse** `buildLabsStudyLinks` and shared shells; **no** parallel lab product IA.

